The '''Civil Aviation Accident and Incident Investigation Commission'''<ref>[http://www.fomento.es/MFOM/LANG_EN/DIRECCIONES_GENERALES/ORGANOS_COLEGIADOS/CIAIAC/default.htm English home page] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913153210/http://www.fomento.es/MFOM/LANG_EN/DIRECCIONES_GENERALES/ORGANOS_COLEGIADOS/CIAIAC/default.htm |date=September 13, 2008 }}." ''Civil Aviation Accident and Incident Investigation Commission''. Retrieved on December 6, 2008.</ref> ({{lang-es|'''Comisión de Investigación de Accidentes e Incidentes de Aviación Civil'''}}, '''CIAIAC''') is the [[Spain|Spanish]] national agency responsible for air accident investigation. It is a division of the [[Ministry of Public Works and Transport (Spain)|Ministry of Public Works and Transport]]. The CIAIAC investigates all the accidents and incidents of civil aircraft that take place in Spanish territory.
The CIAIAC also maintains detailed statistics of all the air accidents and incidents in [[Spain]].
The headquarters of the CIAIAC are in [[Latina (Madrid)|Latina]], [[Madrid]].<ref>"[http://www.fomento.es/MFOM/LANG_EN/DIRECCIONES_GENERALES/ORGANOS_COLEGIADOS/CIAIAC/como_llegar.htm Contáctenos] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100916175628/http://www.fomento.es/MFOM/LANG_EN/DIRECCIONES_GENERALES/ORGANOS_COLEGIADOS/CIAIAC/como_llegar.htm |date=2010-09-16 }}." Civil Aviation Accident and Incident Investigation Commission. Retrieved on September 17, 2010. "Comisión de Investigación de Accidentes e Incidentes de Aviación Civil: C\ Fruela, 6 28011 Madrid" [http://www.fomento.es/NR/rdonlyres/8D4E5BE8-28D0-4347-A69A-E048DAEDBEAA/8220/situacion.gif Direct map link] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720140725/http://www.fomento.es/NR/rdonlyres/8D4E5BE8-28D0-4347-A69A-E048DAEDBEAA/8220/situacion.gif |date=2011-07-20 }} [http://www.fomento.es/NR/rdonlyres/5DB8F5DB-30B7-4BDC-B81B-1931D325356C/8943/edificio1.jpg Direct link to image of headquarters]</ref>
