{{Community and region map of Belgium}}
This is a list of the '''[[Belgium|Belgian]] federal, regional, and community governments'''.

== Federal government ==
{{see also|Belgian Federal Parliament}}
The [[Cabinet of Belgium|Belgian Federal Government]] is the executive branch of the whole Kingdom of [[Belgium]].

{{Belgian federal government}}

== Flemish government ==
{{see also|Flemish Parliament}}

The [[Flemish Government]] is the executive branch of both the [[Flemish Region]] and the [[Flemish Community]].

{{Flemish government}}

== Government of the French Community ==
{{see also|Parliament of the French Community}}

The [[Government of the French Community]] is the executive branch of the [[French Community of Belgium|French Community]].

{{Government of the French Community of Belgium}}

== Government of the German-speaking Community ==
{{see also|Parliament of the German-speaking Community}}

The [[Government of the German-speaking Community]] is the executive branch of the [[German-speaking Community of Belgium|German-speaking Community]].

{{Government of the German-speaking Community of Belgium}}

== Government of the Walloon Region ==
{{see also|Walloon Parliament}}

The Government of the Walloon Region or the [[Walloon Government]] is the executive branch of [[Wallonia]].

{{Walloon Region government}}

== Government of the Brussels-Capital Region ==
{{see also|Parliament of the Brussels-Capital Region}}

The [[Government of the Brussels-Capital Region]] is the executive branch of the [[Brussels-Capital Region]].

{{Government of the Brussels-Capital Region}}

