The '''No Goods and Services Tax Party''' (usually called '''No GST'''), known in 1998 as '''Abolish Child Support''', is a minor [[Australia]]n political party that contested candidates in the [[Australian federal election, 2004|2004 Federal election]]. It was largely a response to the [[John Howard|Howard]] Government's implementation of the [[Goods and Services Tax (Australia)|Goods and Services Tax]]. It polled low totals. [[One Nation (Australia)|One Nation]] founder [[David Ettridge]] contested the [[Australian Senate|Senate]] in Queensland in 2001 for the party.
